definitions.definition: ( in the plural ) The duties or taxes imposed on imported or exported goods .
examples: Customs of £200 were due on all the wine we took back from France.

definitions.definition: ( in the singular or uncountable ) The government department or agency that is authorised to collect the taxes imposed on imported goods .
examples: Customs stopped us in the airport for an inspection.

definitions.definition: The process of going through customs checks at a border checkpoint .
examples: They usually don't care about customs , but she was clearly planning on selling most of it.

definitions.definition: The location at a border checkpoint where customs checks are carried out.
